      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model reliably identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA centrifugal blood pump under CPB use",
      "description": "The validated CFD model, employing the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis index integrated over Lagrangian particle trajectories, is sufficiently credible to rank-order hemolysis severity across the five specified flow-speed combinations and to identify the worst-case operating point for Class II CPB device submissions. The relative hemolysis index (RH) predicted by the model satisfies RH < 1 with respect to the predicate device across all evaluated conditions, supporting regulatory acceptance under 21 CFR 870.4360.",
      "purpose": "Support 510(k) substantial equivalence determination for hemolysis risk",
      "scope": "Five operating points (3–6 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM) for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under CPB conditions"
    }
